1 TITL 1906 Canada Census of Alberta, Saskatchewan, and Manitoba
1 PUBL MyHeritage
1 TEXT The 1906 census was the first regularly scheduled census of the Prairie Provinces. The same census was thereafter conducted every 10 years until 1956. The purpose of this special census was to measure
2 CONC  the high population growth occurring in this part of the country during the first half of the 20th century. Note: records for some sub-districts have not survived; in some instances, this may account
2 CONC  for negative search results.
